<item>
            <title>[SPR-2075] HTML label tag won&apos;t work</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2075</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;(Followup of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1977&quot; title=&quot;Spring-form tags missing &amp;lt;form:label&amp;gt; option&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-1977&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-1977&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The for attribute of a label references the id of the associated control and not the name !&lt;br/&gt;
(see &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/html401/interact/forms.html#h-17.9.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.w3.org/TR/html401/interact/forms.html#h-17.9.1&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, the current implementation of the label tag won&apos;t work, because it sets the for attribute to the path expression which is used as the name for controls and not as the id.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
